  "texts": [
    "Table 1 shows the number of trainable parameters, training time, and performance on MMLU and MedMCQA for models of each size when fully finetuned versus fine-tuned with FFN blocks frozen, referred to as MoFE.",
    "When fully fine-tuning, the number of trainable parameters increases with the number of expert models.",
    "However, in MoFE, the number of trainable parameters remains constant regardless of the number of expert models.",
    "This results in a fixed training time for MoFE models, while training time increases with model size for models with fully updated FFN blocks.",
    "Notably, even for the small model with 2 expert models, MoFE requires less than half the training time compared to fully updating the model."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}